The paper discusses clustering techniques applied to web usage mining, which involves analyzing user behavior on a website. This falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses various validity and accuracy measures for evaluating clustering performance, which falls under the statistics (cs.ST) and databases (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on user navigational sessions, which suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
